<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="774" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 195.1/43</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Ambassador in Brazil</gloss>
                            </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-14T18:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Steamer <persName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Robert Dollar</hi>
                            </persName> was given provisional certificate of registration as
                            American vessel several days since by American Consul <pb facs="0807" n="493" xml:id="pg_493"/> General, Rio de Janiero, under
                            instructions transmitted by this Department showing that vessel had
                            regularly been transferred to American ownership and entitled to
                            American registration under laws of United States. Reported that vessel
                            denied clearance by Brazilian authorities.</p>
                        <p>Investigate and request release and clearance of vessel, that it may
                            proceed at once to American port.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>